NEWS
  Show empire news since your last login (or the last N days).

SYNTAX
  news
  news <days>

DESCRIPTION
  Displays a log of events that have happened in the empire since the
  last time you read the news.  Events include diplomatic declarations,
  combat results, and sector captures.

  With no argument, shows news since you last ran "news".
  With a number, shows news from the last N days (e.g. "news 3" = last
  3 days of events).

  News is organized into sections:
    Foreign Affairs   — diplomatic declarations, alliance/war changes
    The Front Line    — land combat results, sector captures
    The High Seas     — naval combat and assault landings
    Sky Watch         — air combat (future)
    Telecommunications — telegrams sent (not shown by default)

  The Bottom Line section (at the end) shows a net summary of sectors
  captured between pairs of nations.

  Your news-read timestamp is updated each time you run "news", so the
  next call will only show events since this call.

EXAMPLE
  news              show news since last read
  news 1            show all news from the last day

SEE ALSO
  headlines  relations  declare

